@lamsgarden0229 is a zi char restaurant famous for its Twin Towers Crispy Noodles.

For this period, they are offering islandwide delivery. Drive-through and takeaway is available too:
• Call or Whatsapp +65 9638 6387 to order
• Delivery Fee: $5 nett
• Minimum Order: $15
• Ordering Hours: Daily 11am to 10pm (last order 9pm)

My favourite dish was definitely the signature Twin Towers Crispy Noodles ($10)! This striking dish consists of two “sheng mian towers” perched on a broth filled with sliced fish, clams, and prawns.

The broth was savoury, flavourful, and thick, clinging onto every strand of the crispy noodles. They were quite generous with the seafood too. Overall a very satisfying dish.

Lam’s Garden offers quality zi char dishes at reasonable prices. $5 islandwide delivery fee is really cheap, and the minimum order of $15 is lower than many other restaurants in Singapore. This is definitely a good option for delivery if you’re having a craving for Chinese comfort food.

Read more via link in bio.

Disclosure: Lam’s Garden paid for the food featured.
